HEADWORD: Heteronymous
<hw>Het`er*on"y*mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hetero-</ets> + Gr. <grk>"o`nyma</grk>, for
<grk>"o`noma</grk> a name.]</ety> <def>Having different names or
designations; standing in opposite relations.</def> <rj><au>J. Le
Conte.</au></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Het"er*on"y*mous*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

